<br>
Once you've gotten SoW, you can kite duos with little to no problem. If you get a clarity or breeze, you can start pulling three's and four's. Remember, Multi-Kiting isn't always killing the maximum amount of targets all the time. At low levels, you'll be stuck dealing with less targets, but the exp is still better then root/nuking, and it'll give you lots of practice for the rest of the game. <p><center><IMG SRC=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/jarninsigpic2.jpg><br><center><Br>Grand Master Fisherman<Br>Master Brewer<Br>Master Chef<Br>Master of Begging<Br><Br><b>AL`KABOR IS A SISSY!</b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utegellan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tegellan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/25/01 4:26:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=186.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Low level multi-kiting</span><hr size=1>  Haha, I almost feel like making a new wizard just to try this at the lower levels <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
